article.headline: George Mason 66, Delaware 46
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Will Thomas scored a team-high 14 points, and grabbed nine rebounds, and George Mason stomped Delaware 66-46 Wednesday night. George Mason (14-12, 8-8 CAA), which snapped a three-game losing streak, hit 25 of 52 shots from the field, 6 of 15 three-pointers, and held a 37-29 advantage on the boards while allowing only nine turnovers. "This was one of those nights when our shots wouldn't go in and we let that affect us on the defensive end," said Delaware head coach Monte Ross, whose team shot just 16 of 51 from the field for the game, including 8 of 28 (28.6 percent) in the opening half. Herb Courtney scored a game-high 19 points for Delaware (5-22, 3-13).
